My first foster kittens have moved on, so here’s a photo dump. 

This experience showed me a lot about life, love and definitely patience. So grateful Kerri initiated me into this world, and taught me every step of the way. I can’t wait for our next ones.

If you are in AZ and want to adopt these sweet boys, they will be available Wednesday at AZ Humane Society. 

I’ll be publishing a zine about the process soon.

Photo dump of the best October of my life so far.
Witnessing the oppression faced by many clouds what little beauty exists in our world. Yet, I'm thankful for the pockets of joy my family and I have discovered throughout November.

2023 was a standout year for music for me. While I only made it to 42 show, far short of my goal, it spanned a spectrum of 121 bands. The year was marked by gritty, authentic performances, like Spike Hellis’ intense shows on both coasts, Hallows, Panther Modern, Sextile, and Choke Chain really brought the energy. Void Vision’s daring Madonna reinterpretation was a moment I wish I could relive over and over. Catching Protocultura and La Pregunta multiple times, hanging out with Casey Royer and seeing many old friends and making new ones, especially at the Rubycon shows made it all so worth it. 

The tour trails of Puerte Negra and Un Hombre Solo across California showcased the raw edge of this culture I hold close to my heart. Notably, intimate encounters with icons like The Cure, and the avant-garde stylings of The Human League and Danny Elfman, punctuated the year. 

Beyond the music, it was a deep dive into the heart of the ATL, Philly, Los Angeles and Phoenix scenes, often in the company of Kerri. So grateful we both hold this music and life so close to our heart.
